  "The logarithm with base e, the inverse of e^x": "与基对数 e 的对数, e x 的对数",
  "Any logarithm used in nature": "用于自然性质的任何对数",
  "The natural logarithm ln(x) is the logarithm with base e. It is the inverse function of e^x, meaning if y = e^x, then x = ln(y). Its derivative is 1/x.": "自然对数 In( x) 是使用基数的对数 e。 这是 e x 的反函数, 这意味着如果 y = e x, 那么 x = In(y) 。 它的衍生物为 1/x 。",
  "What does Euler's number 'e' represent?": "欧拉的号码\"e\"代表什么?",
  "The square root of 2": "2 的平方根",
  "An irrational constant approximately 2.71828 that is the base of natural logarithms": "一个非理性常数约2.71828 这是自然对数的基础",
  "The ratio of a circle's circumference to its diameter": "圆圆环环与直径之比",
  "The golden ratio": "金比金比",
  "Euler's number e is approximately 2.71828. It can be defined as lim(n->infinity)(1 + 1/n)^n. It is the unique base for which d/dx[a^x] = a^x, making it fundamental in calculus.": "Euler的编号e约为2.71828,可定义为lim(n->infinity)(1+1/n)n。它是 d/dx[ax] =ax的独特基数,在微积分中具有根本意义。",
  "What does 'exponential growth' mean?": "\"快速增长\"是什么意思?",
  "Growth that follows a linear pattern": "沿着线性模式增长的增长",
  "Growth at a constant rate": "以恒定增长率",
  "Growth that eventually stops": "最终停止增长的增长",
  "Growth where the rate of increase is proportional to the current amount": "增长率与当前数额成正比的增长率",
  "Exponential growth occurs when a quantity increases at a rate proportional to its current value, modeled by dy/dt = ky, with solution y = Ce^(kt). The derivative of e^(kt) is ke^(kt), which is k times the original function.": "指数增长发生时,数量增长与其当前值成正比,以 dy/dt = ky为模型,且有 y = Ce(kt) 。e(kt) 的衍生物为 k(kt) , 即 k乘以原函数。",
  "What does 'exponential decay' mean?": "\"衰变\"是什么意思?",
  "A quantity that becomes negative": "数量变为负数",
  "A quantity that decreases linearly over time": "随时间而线性减少的数量",
  "A quantity that decreases at a rate proportional to its current value": "以与其现值成比例的速率减少的数量",
  "A quantity that decreases to zero instantly": "立即降至零的数量",
  "Exponential decay is modeled by y = Ce^(-kt) where k > 0. The quantity decreases at a rate proportional to itself (dy/dt = -ky), approaching zero but never reaching it.": "指数衰变由 y = Ce(- kt) 模拟, k > 0。 数量下降速度与其本身成比例( dy/ dt = -ky) , 接近零, 但从未达到 。",
  "What does 'half-life' mean in the context of exponential decay?": "在指数衰变的情况下,“半衰期”意味着什么?",
  "The time for a quantity to reduce to half its original value": "某一数量将其原价值减半的时间",
  "Half the time it takes for a quantity to reach zero": "数量达到零需要一半的时间",
  "The time for a quantity to double": "数量翻倍的时间",
  "50% of the initial value": "初始值的50%",
  "Half-life is the time required for a quantity undergoing exponential decay to decrease to half its initial amount. If y = Ce^(-kt), the half-life is t_(1/2) = ln(2)/k.": "半衰期是正在发生指数衰减的数量将初始数量减半所需的时间。如果y = Ce(-kt),则半衰期为 t_(1/2) = In(2)/k。",
  "What is the 'change of base formula' for logarithms?": "对数的“ 基公式变化” 是什么 ?",
  "log_a(x) = ln(a) / ln(x)": "log_a(x) = In(a) / In(x)",
